<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued March 31 at 1:23PM EDT until March 31 at 1:45PM EDT by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 PM EDT
FOR WEST CENTRAL NICHOLAS...SOUTH CENTRAL CLAY AND NORTH CENTRAL
FAYETTE COUNTIES...
At 123 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Gauley Bridge,
or 13 miles north of Fayetteville, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Damage to trees and power lines.
Locations impacted include...
Bentree, Swiss, Kesslers Cross Lanes, and Drennan.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.
Please report severe weather by calling 412-262-1988, posting to
the NWS Pittsburgh Facebook page, or using Twitter @NWSPITTSBURGH.</instruction>
